TO THE DEALERSHIP?

00:40.340 --> 00:41.932
DON'T, UH,
DON'T BE ALARMED, SIR.

00:41.970 --> 00:43.801
WE'RE, UH,
WE'RE TRAINED PROFESSIONALS.

00:43.840 --> 00:46.229
(man) * I BEGGED HER PLEASE *

00:46.280 --> 00:48.805
SLAM DUNK!
TRACI'S GOT IT IN THE BAG.

00:48.840 --> 00:50.239
DEPENDS WHO ELSE APPLIED.

00:50.280 --> 00:51.474
NO, IT DOESN'T.
YES, IT DOES.

00:51.510 --> 00:53.978
SHE HAS BEEN IN NIGHT SCHOOL
FOR THREE MONTHS.

00:54.020 --> 00:55.442
SHE'S LITERALLY TAKEN
EVERY CLASS

00:55.480 --> 00:56.617
WITH THE WORD "DETECTIVE"
IN THE TITLE.

00:56.650 --> 00:58.288
DOESN'T MATI'ER.
YOU KNOW WHAT MATTERS?

00:58.320 --> 00:59.685
PERSONALITY.

00:59.720 --> 01:02.086
IS SHE SOMEONE YOU'D WANT
TO BE STUCK IN A VAN WITH

01:02.130 --> 01:03.256
ALL DAY, DAY AFI'ER DAY?
(chuckles)

01:03.290 --> 01:04.689
THAT'S THE DECIDING FACTOR.
LIKE I SAID,

01:04.730 --> 01:06.197
SHE HAS GOT IT IN THE BAG.

01:06.230 --> 01:07.322
RIGHT. SHE'S GOT IT ALL?

01:07.360 --> 01:09.055
MM-HMM.
YEAH.

01:09.100 --> 01:10.499
PERSONALITY!

01:10.530 --> 01:13.465
(laughs) SHUT UP.

01:13.500 --> 01:15.639
STOP. STOP.
PLEASE STOP THE CAR.
WHAT? WHAT? WHAT?

01:15.670 --> 01:16.705
WHAT HAPPENED?
SAM, STOP.

01:16.740 --> 01:18.662
(brakes squeal)

01:21.410 --> 01:22.707
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

01:22.750 --> 01:24.672
WHAT DO I WANT?
IT'S NOT EVEN 10:00 AM.
YEAH.

01:24.710 --> 01:26.143
WHAT'S YOUR POINT?

01:26.180 --> 01:28.410
COME ON. IT'S HOT.
IT'S SUMMER.

01:28.450 --> 01:29.849
* AT LEAST FOR NOW *

01:29.890 --> 01:30.845
* AT LEAST FOR NOW *

01:30.890 --> 01:32.482
* TILL I CAN FIND THE STREET *

01:32.520 --> 01:33.714
* FIND THE STREET *

01:33.760 --> 01:35.318
* SHE SPED DOWN *

01:35.360 --> 01:36.486
* SHE SPED DOWN *

01:36.530 --> 01:37.986
* I LOST MY KEYS *

01:38.030 --> 01:39.156
* I LOST MY KEYS *

01:39.200 --> 01:40.519
* IT DIDN'T TAKE LONG *

01:40.560 --> 01:41.720
* IT DIDN'T TAKE LONG *

01:41.760 --> 01:43.227
* SHE'S A SOUR DREAM *

01:43.270 --> 01:44.294
* SHE'S A SOUR DREAM *

01:44.330 --> 01:45.661
OKAY, SO I'M A LITTLE RUSTY.

01:45.700 --> 01:48.191
I CALLED YOU ONCE, TEXTED
YOU TWICE, DIDN'T HEAR BACK.

01:48.240 --> 01:50.128
YOU'RE TESTING ME, RIGHT?

01:50.170 --> 01:51.808
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

01:51.840 --> 01:53.205
I'M SUPPOSED TO TAKE IT
AS A CHALLENGE.

01:53.240 --> 01:54.798
IT'S ALL COMING BACK TO ME.

01:54.840 --> 01:57.377
(indistinct conversations,
radio chatter)

01:57.410 --> 01:58.900
(whispers) WOW.

01:58.950 --> 02:01.418
(normal voice) TOTALLY DEADPAN.
THAT'S ACTUALLY IMPRESSIVE.

02:01.450 --> 02:02.417
(door closes)

02:02.450 --> 02:05.817
UH, THE OTHER NIGHT,
YOU AND ME?

02:05.850 --> 02:07.989
(chuckles) OH, YEAH.

02:08.020 --> 02:10.329
PFFI'. I REALLY SHOULDN'T
DRINK TEQUILA,

02:10.360 --> 02:12.658
'CAUSE I KINDA DO
STUPID THINGS... (chuckles)

02:12.700 --> 02:14.156
SO... (blows raspberry)

02:14.200 --> 02:17.089
(telephone rings in distance)

02:17.130 --> 02:18.461
(sniffles)
UH, TODAY'S SPECIAL IS

02:18.500 --> 02:22.766
THE EIGHTH ANNUAL JAMESTOWN,
UH, STREETBALL TOURN EY.

02:22.810 --> 02:24.402
ALL RIGHT.
THERE'S FOUR TEAMS, FIVE GAMES.

02:24.440 --> 02:25.862
PASSIONS ARE GONNA RUN HIGH.

02:25.910 --> 02:27.275
LAST COUPLE OF YEARS,
THERE HAVE BEEN SOME SCUFFLES,

02:27.310 --> 02:29.301
OF COURSE,
AND, UH, ONE STABBING.

02:29.350 --> 02:33.138
THIS YEAR THE VISITING TEAM IS
FROM THE EAST END, FROM MALVERN,

02:33.180 --> 02:34.977
SO IF THEY HUMILIATE
THE LOCAL BOYS,

02:35.020 --> 02:36.317
WE COULD BE BUSY.

02:36.350 --> 02:39.046
I'LL BE WORKING THIS ONE,
KEEPING TABS.

02:39.090 --> 02:42.821
MY OLD NEIGHBORHOOD,
SO DON'T EMBARRASS ME,

02:42.860 --> 02:44.623
AND ONE MORE THING.

02:44.660 --> 02:47.823
WE'LL BE MAKING A DECISION
BY END OF DAY ON WHO'S LANDING

02:47.860 --> 02:50.169
THE 6-MONTH ROTATION
WITH THE, UH, DETECT IVES...

02:50.200 --> 02:51.997
(coughs) NASH.
(Andy, lowered voice)
GO, TRACI!

02:52.030 --> 02:55.295
SO IF ANYONE ELSE WANTS
TO BE CONSIDERED,

02:55.340 --> 02:57.365
I NEED IT IN WRITING TODAY.

02:57.410 --> 02:58.536
PECK.

02:58.570 --> 03:00.936
APPLICATIONS--TH EY COME
DIRECTLY TO YOU, SIR?

03:00.980 --> 03:02.641
SOONER THE BE'I'I'ER.

03:02.680 --> 03:04.045
YOUR ASSIGNMENTS ARE
ON THE BOARD,

03:04.080 --> 03:05.479
SO LET'S GO, PEOPLE...
(claps hands)

03:05.510 --> 03:07.216
AND STAY COOL OUT THERE.

03:07.250 --> 03:09.684
(indistinct conversations)

03:09.720 --> 03:11.517
GAIL. GAIL.

03:13.360 --> 03:15.612
YOU'RE NOT SERIOUSLY THINKING
OF APPLYING, ARE YOU?

03:15.660 --> 03:17.981
YOU'RE NOT QUALIFIED.

03:18.030 --> 03:19.554
AND YOU ARE?

03:19.600 --> 03:21.898
YEAH, 'CAUSE I'VE BEEN
BUSTIN' MY ASS FOR MONTHS.

03:21.930 --> 03:23.818
I'VE BEEN TAKING
ALL THE COURSES.

03:23.870 --> 03:25.963
WELL, THEN I'M SURE
YOU WILL GET IT.

03:26.000 --> 03:27.297
(radio chatter)

03:27.340 --> 03:28.295
SHE'S JUST MESSING WITH YOU.

03:28.340 --> 03:30.205
(sighs)
JERRY, SHE'S CONNECTED.

03:30.240 --> 03:31.969
SHE--SHE'S A PECK.

03:32.010 --> 03:32.977
MM-HMM.

03:33.010 --> 03:34.136
SHE COULD SCOOP THIS THING.

03:34.180 --> 03:36.375
WELL, YOU HAVE DONE
EVERYTHING RIGHT,

03:36.410 --> 03:38.139
SO WHAT WILL BE WILL BE.

03:38.180 --> 03:40.319
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

03:40.350 --> 03:41.977
TRACE, YOU'RE WIGGIN' OUT.
RELAX. (chuckles)

03:42.020 --> 03:44.318
IT'S A BEAUTIFUL DAY.

03:45.990 --> 03:47.480
(clicks)

03:47.520 --> 03:49.659
SO, WHAT, BUYER'S REMORSE?

03:49.690 --> 03:51.328
YOU'RE PLEADING
TEMPORARY INSANITY?

03:51.360 --> 03:53.328
YEAH. MORE OR LESS.

03:53.360 --> 03:55.157
I DON'T BUY IT.
I THINK YOU'RE TERRIFIED.

03:55.200 --> 03:57.122
I THINK YOU'VE FORGOTTEN
HOW GOOD WE ARE TOGETHER,

03:57.170 --> 03:58.194
AND NOW YOU'RE FREAKIN' OUT.

03:58.230 --> 04:00.039
YOU NAILED IT.
I'M FREAKING OUT.

04:00.070 --> 04:01.037
LET'S GO, PRETTY BOY.

04:01.070 --> 04:02.958
YES, SIR.

04:03.010 --> 04:04.830
WILLIAMS,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

04:04.870 --> 04:07.338
FOUR SHIFTS IN A ROW
STUCK INSIDE.

04:07.380 --> 04:09.302
ARE YOU TRYING TO BENCH ME?

04:09.350 --> 04:10.578
OF COURSE NOT.

04:10.610 --> 04:11.577
I SWITCHED WITH NASH.

04:11.610 --> 04:13.475
I TOLD HER YOU'D BE FINE
WITH IT.

04:13.520 --> 04:16.171
I'M PREGNANT, FRANK.
I'M NOT MADE OF GLASS.

04:21.460 --> 04:22.427
OKAY, I KNOW THAT
THE NEIGHBORHOOD HAS

04:22.460 --> 04:23.427
A LOT OF GANGS,
BUT, UH, COME ON.

04:23.460 --> 04:25.189
IT'S THEIR KIDS,
THEIR FAMILIES.

04:25.230 --> 04:26.185
SO?

04:26.230 --> 04:27.390
SO THEY'D HAVE TO GET BEAT
PRETTY BAD

04:27.430 --> 04:28.897
IF THEY WERE GONNA
START SOMETHING.

04:28.930 --> 04:32.331
THAT'S WHAT I LOVE
ABOUT YOU, MCNALLY.

04:32.370 --> 04:35.635
WHAT, MY NAIVE BELIEF
IN HUMANITY?

04:35.670 --> 04:37.706
YOUR RELENTLESS OPTIMISM

04:37.740 --> 04:39.970
IN THE FACE OF EXPERIENCE,
RESEARCH, AND REALITY.

04:40.010 --> 04:41.170
PFFI'.

04:41.210 --> 04:44.304
THAT TAKES STONES,
BIG PEOPLE-LOVING STONES.

04:44.350 --> 04:46.875
OH, WELL, SOMEBODY'S GOTTA
LOVE 'EM.

04:46.920 --> 04:49.980
THIS NEIGHBORHOOD IS FULL
OF GANG MEMBERS.

04:50.020 --> 04:52.818
THEY'RE ALL SUPERFANS.
THEY LOVE THE GAME.

04:52.860 --> 04:55.385
THEY LOVE THEIR TEAMS.
THEY HATE TO LOSE.

04:55.420 --> 04:57.786
JUST LIKE US
WHEN WE PLAY 27 DIVISION.

04:57.830 --> 05:00.594
(chuckles) WELL...
LET'S JUST STAY VISIBLE

05:00.630 --> 05:02.894
AND LET 'EM KNOW
WE'RE HERE, WE'RE WATCHIN'.

05:02.930 --> 05:04.659
YEP, YEP, YEP.

05:04.700 --> 05:05.928
(indistinct conversations)

05:05.970 --> 05:07.437
IT'S A FAMILY EVENT.
THERE'S KIDS HERE.

05:07.470 --> 05:09.836
EVERYBODY'S HAVING
A GOOD TIME TODAY, GUARANTEED.

05:09.870 --> 05:11.098
ATTABOY. ALL RIGHT, CARL.

05:11.140 --> 05:12.300
IT'S GOOD YOU'RE HERE.
THANK YOU, PAL.

05:12.340 --> 05:14.137
YOU SHOW UP IN COLORS,
YOU GET BOUNCED.

05:14.180 --> 05:15.306
EXCELLENT. OKAY.
NO PROBLEM.

05:15.340 --> 05:16.500
NOW I'LL TELL--
I'LL HOLD YOU TO THAT.

05:16.550 --> 05:18.802
BIG FELLA RIGHT THERE--
THAT'S DOOBIE.

05:18.850 --> 05:20.169
YOU DON'T WANT TO MESS
WITH DOOBIE.

05:20.220 --> 05:21.812
EX-ARMY.

05:21.850 --> 05:23.249
YEAH? WHAT UNIT?

05:23.290 --> 05:24.917
YOU KNOW, THE MARINES
OR WHATEVER, FOR REAL.

05:24.950 --> 05:26.087
FOR REAL, HUH?
FOR REAL, HUH?

05:26.120 --> 05:27.087
FOR REAL, I'M NOT MESSING
WITH DOOBIE.

05:27.120 --> 05:28.087
(laughs)

05:28.120 --> 05:29.087
THANK YOU.
TAKE CARE.

05:29.120 --> 05:30.485
WHOA.
(children laugh)

05:30.530 --> 05:32.088
(chuckles)

05:32.130 --> 05:34.098
(indistinct conversations,
siren wailing in distance)

05:34.130 --> 05:35.757
SERGEANT BEST!

05:35.800 --> 05:38.098
***

05:38.130 --> 05:39.768
AREN'T YOU LOOKING GOOD?

05:39.800 --> 05:42.633
ROLAND JONES.

05:42.670 --> 05:44.399
IT'S STAFF SERGEANT NOW.

05:44.440 --> 05:45.907
OH, IS THAT RIGHT?
YEAH, THAT'S RIGHT.

05:45.940 --> 05:48.807
(both laugh)

05:48.840 --> 05:50.102
YOU'RE A JOKER, MAN.

05:50.150 --> 05:51.902
HOW ARE YOU DOIN', MAN?
WHEN DID YOU GET OUT?

05:51.950 --> 05:54.145
SUNDAY MORNING, YO.
GOD BLESS THE SYSTEM.

05:54.180 --> 05:56.648
THE JUDGE GIVES ME EIGHT YEARS.
I'M OUT IN TWO, YOU KNOW?

05:56.690 --> 05:58.180
(laughs)

05:58.220 --> 06:00.359
AND YOU'RE RIGHT BACK
IN THE BUSINESS, HUH?

06:00.390 --> 06:02.483
NO, MAN. NO, MAN. I'M DONE
WITH THE DRUG DEALING, MAN.

06:02.530 --> 06:04.418
THAT'S A YOUNG MAN'S GAME.
THEY CAN HAVE THAT.

06:04.460 --> 06:05.427
YOU'RE DONE?

06:05.460 --> 06:06.996
YEAH, MAN. YEAH, I'M DONE.

06:07.030 --> 06:09.225
LET'S DO SOME ONE-ON-ONE.
COME. PLAY SOME BASKETBALL.

06:09.260 --> 06:11.399
(chuckles) I'D STILL KICK
YOUR ASS, JONES.

06:12.400 --> 06:14.391
TELL YOU WHAT.

06:15.670 --> 06:17.308
YOU LET ME KNOW IF THERE'S
ANYTHING GOING DOWN,

06:17.340 --> 06:19.308
ANY RUMBLE ON THE STREET.

06:19.340 --> 06:21.137
WHY WOULD I DO THAT,
FRANK?

06:21.180 --> 06:23.148
'CAUSE YOU'RE SMART.

06:23.180 --> 06:25.546
YOU'RE OUT ON PAROLE.
I'M SURE YOU WANT TO STAY OUT.

06:25.580 --> 06:28.140
GOD BLESS THE SYSTEM.

06:28.180 --> 06:29.647
YEAH, GOD BLESS THE SYSTEM.

06:29.690 --> 06:31.339
BUT YOU SEE
THEM DEVILS THERE?

06:31.390 --> 06:32.880
THEY'RE GONNA WIN
THE WHOLE THING.

06:32.920 --> 06:33.989
(Roland)
YOU CAN PUT MONEY ON THAT.

06:34.020 --> 06:35.317
* IN THE COUNTRY BAR *

06:35.360 --> 06:36.657
* THAT GIRL--SHE WITH ME *

06:36.690 --> 06:38.180
* SHE LOVE THIS BOY *

06:38.230 --> 06:39.356
YEAH, I DON'T KNOW, MAN.

06:39.390 --> 06:41.426
LOOK, DETECTIVE JOB IS
ALL PAPERWORK, YOU KNOW?

06:41.460 --> 06:43.064
I WANT TO BE OUT
ON THE FRONT LINES

06:43.100 --> 06:45.989
TALKING TO PEOPLE, YOU KNOW?
THAT'S WHERE THE ACTION IS.

06:46.030 --> 06:47.133
(radio chatter,
horn honking in distance)

06:47.170 --> 06:49.297
(chuckles)

06:49.340 --> 06:50.307
DOV?

06:50.340 --> 06:51.466
SORRY?

06:51.510 --> 06:53.637
(chuckles)

06:53.680 --> 06:55.807
YOU STILL THINKING
ABOUT THAT CAR?

06:55.840 --> 06:59.139
YOU KNOW, I'M OFFICIALLY
THREE YEARS AHEAD OF SCHEDULE.

06:59.180 --> 07:00.408
ALL RIGHT,
FIRST DAY AT THE ACADEMY,

07:00.450 --> 07:02.042
I HAD THIS PICTURE OF WHERE
I WANTED MY LIFE TO BE

07:02.080 --> 07:03.240
IN FIVE YEARS--

07:03.290 --> 07:07.408
AMAZING JOB, AMAZING FRIENDS,
BEAUTIFUL GIRLFRIEND.

07:07.460 --> 07:08.654
FEELS GOOD?

07:08.690 --> 07:09.782
THERE'S ONLY ONE THING

07:09.830 --> 07:12.151
THAT COULD POSSIBLY MAKE
MY LIFE ANY BETTER.

07:12.190 --> 07:15.091
LICORICE. I NEED LICORICE.
(chuckles)

07:15.130 --> 07:16.859
NICE.

07:22.370 --> 07:23.803
(seat belt clicks)

07:23.840 --> 07:26.161
OH, AND, UH, MAKE SURE
IT'S FRESH. IT'S GOTTA BE FRESH.

07:26.210 --> 07:27.973
IF IT'S NOT FRESH--
THERE'S NO POINT.

07:28.010 --> 07:30.706
(chuckles) YEAH.
OH, AND GRAB ME A GINGER ALE.

07:32.680 --> 07:33.772
MORNING, SIR.

07:33.820 --> 07:35.913
OFFICER. BE RIGHT THERE.

07:35.950 --> 07:37.815
(radio chatter)

07:37.850 --> 07:39.317
(clears throat)

07:39.350 --> 07:42.353
***

07:44.530 --> 07:46.691
YOU GUYS HAVE ANY LICORICE?

07:51.970 --> 07:53.130
(clatters)

07:53.170 --> 07:54.467
YOU WORK HERE?

07:54.500 --> 07:57.469
YEAH. (panting)

07:57.510 --> 07:59.000
YEAH?

08:00.840 --> 08:03.502
YOU MIND STEPPING OUT
FROM BEHIND THE COUNTER, PLEASE?

