(siren wailing)

09:03.170 --> 09:04.467
THE PRESSURE BANDAGE.
(unZIps bag)

09:04.510 --> 09:06.068
IS HE BREAT_HING?
(Dov panting)

09:06.110 --> 09:07.805
I CAN'T TELL.

09:07.840 --> 09:10.172
(siren whoops)

09:10.210 --> 09:11.177
(woman) WHAT DO WE HAVE?

09:11.210 --> 09:13.349
HE'S BEHIND THE COUNTER.

09:13.380 --> 09:16.178
GUNSHOT WOUND,
UPPER LEFT SIDE.

09:16.220 --> 09:19.485
OKAY, I GOT THIS,
SO JUST... MOVE. MOVE!

09:19.520 --> 09:20.817
OKAY.

09:20.860 --> 09:21.815
(unzips bag)

09:21.860 --> 09:22.986
HE STILL HAS VITAL SIGNS.

09:23.030 --> 09:25.157
(radio chatter)

09:28.530 --> 09:31.328
OKAY. UH, SIR. SIR.
OKAY. THANK YOU.

09:31.370 --> 09:32.496
WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO GET
YOU OUTSIDE, OKAY?

09:32.530 --> 09:34.066
SIR, COME ON.
(siren wailing)

09:34.100 --> 09:35.431
NO, NO.
SIR, OVER HERE, PLEASE.

09:35.470 --> 09:37.199
YOU'RE JUST GONNA HAVE
TO WAIT HERE FOR A MOMENT.

09:39.210 --> 09:40.438
(gears shift)

09:40.480 --> 09:41.572
(radio chatter)

09:41.610 --> 09:42.907
(Chris) JUST STAY RIGHT HERE,
SIR, OKAY?

09:42.950 --> 09:44.178
SOMEONE'S GONNA BE HERE
TO QUESTION YOU IN A MOMENT.

09:44.210 --> 09:45.677
(pants) HEY, YOU GUYS.
ARE YOU GUYS OKAY?

09:45.710 --> 09:48.270
YEAH. WE'RE FINE.

09:48.320 --> 09:49.275
(siren wailing in distance)

09:49.320 --> 09:50.287
WHAT HAPPENED?

09:50.320 --> 09:52.140
I WALKED IN ON A ROBBERY
IN PROGRESS.

09:52.190 --> 09:53.259
THE KID HAD A GUN.

09:53.290 --> 09:54.257
YOU SHOT HIM?

09:54.290 --> 09:56.315
YES.

09:56.360 --> 09:57.327
DIAZ, WHERE WERE YOU?

09:57.360 --> 09:58.327
(Chris) I WAS OUTSIDE.

09:58.360 --> 09:59.327
AND WHO'S THIS?

09:59.360 --> 10:00.327
THIS IS THE CLERK.

10:00.360 --> 10:01.327
ANYONE ELSE INSIDE?

10:01.360 --> 10:02.759
NO.

10:02.800 --> 10:05.064
ALL RIGHT. LISTEN UP.
WE NEED TO SEPARATE YOU.

10:05.100 --> 10:06.897
PUT EPSTEIN IN A SQUAD CAR.

10:06.940 --> 10:08.669
MAKE SURE HE'S CLEANED UP,
ALL RIGHT?
OKAY.

10:08.700 --> 10:10.133
DOV, LET'S GO.
DIAZ, YOU GET IN OUR SQUAD CAR.

10:10.170 --> 10:11.762
YOU DO NOT TALK TO ANYONE.
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

10:11.810 --> 10:12.777
YES.
YES?

10:12.810 --> 10:15.074
YES.
GO.

10:16.110 --> 10:17.441
WHAT'S YOUR NAME, SIR?

10:17.480 --> 10:18.879
TREVOR SANTOS.
OKAY, MR. SANTOS,

10:18.910 --> 10:20.775
I NEED YOU
TO STAY RIGHT HERE, OKAY?
YEAH.

10:20.820 --> 10:21.809
ALL RIGHT?
YEAH.

10:21.850 --> 10:23.841
THIS IS JUST
STANDARD PROCEDURE, OKAY?

10:23.890 --> 10:25.642
(siren whoops)
JUST TO ISOLATE YOU,
SO YOU DON'T CONTAMINATE

10:25.690 --> 10:26.657
EACH OTHER'S EVIDENCE.

10:26.690 --> 10:27.759
YEAH. NO, I KNOW. I KNOW.
OKAY.

10:27.790 --> 10:28.757
FRANK, I'M ON SCENE.
(sighs)

10:28.790 --> 10:29.757
FRONT OR BACK?

10:29.790 --> 10:31.087
(siren whoops)
WHAT?

10:31.130 --> 10:32.927
WHERE SHOULD I SIT?
FRONT OR BACK?
(Siren walling)

10:32.960 --> 10:34.894
FRONT.
(opens door)

10:34.930 --> 10:37.922
(gears shift, radio chatter)

10:39.070 --> 10:41.129
(siren wailing in distance)
McNALLY, WHERE IS CHRIS?

10:41.170 --> 10:42.239
UH, HE'S IN THE CAR.
(door closes)

10:42.270 --> 10:43.828
COLLINS.

10:45.170 --> 10:46.467
YOU'RE GONNA GET
THE YELLOW TAPE OUT,

10:46.510 --> 10:47.932
AND YOU'RE GONNA SET UP
THE PERIMETER, OKAY?

10:47.980 --> 10:49.675
THERE'S GONNA BE
AN EVEN BIGGER CROWD SOON,

10:49.710 --> 10:50.870
AND WE ARE NOT GIVING OUT
ANY INFORMATION.

10:50.910 --> 10:52.775
GOT IT.
OKAY? DO IT. MOVE.

10:52.820 --> 10:54.219
(creaks)

10:54.250 --> 10:55.239
(radio chatter)
(woman) ON THREE.

10:55.280 --> 10:56.941
READY?

10:56.990 --> 10:59.242
ONE... TWO... THREE...

10:59.290 --> 11:01.281
LIFT.
(gurney rattles)

11:01.320 --> 11:04.323
OKAY, BAG THE SHIRT.
THE DOCTOR WILL WANT TO SEE IT.

11:04.360 --> 11:05.884
OKAY, LET'S ROLL HIM OUT.

11:09.030 --> 11:11.999
(rattling)

11:12.030 --> 11:15.158
(siren wailing,
emergency vehicle horn honking)

11:15.200 --> 11:17.009
OKAY.

11:17.040 --> 11:19.463
S.I.U. IS GONNA
QUESTION YOU BOTH

11:19.510 --> 11:23.002
ON, UM, EVERYTHING THEY CAN
THINK OF, REALLY,

11:23.050 --> 11:25.006
AND THE INVESTIGATION
IS GONNA TAKE

11:25.050 --> 11:27.177
ABOUT A COUPLE OF WEEKS.

11:27.220 --> 11:31.008
UM, YOU'LL BE
ON ADMINISTRATIVE DUTY,

11:31.050 --> 11:32.517
BUT THEN YOU'LL BE CLEARED,

11:32.550 --> 11:34.313
AND EVERYTHING WILL GO
BACK TO NORMAL.

11:34.360 --> 11:36.988
THEY'RE RUSHING--
THE E.M.T.s.

11:37.030 --> 11:39.828
THAT'S GOOD.
MEANS HE'S ALIVE, RIGHT?

11:39.860 --> 11:40.997
(ambulance door closes)

11:41.030 --> 11:42.657
YEP.

11:42.700 --> 11:43.962
(knock on hood)

11:44.000 --> 11:45.797
COME HERE.

11:45.830 --> 11:48.492
(opens door)

11:48.540 --> 11:51.532
(horn honks, siren wailing)

11:53.410 --> 11:56.777
EPSTEIN, THIS IS ALEX MORELAND
FROM S.I.U.

11:56.810 --> 11:59.938
OFFICER EPSTEIN, I'M GONNA NEED
YOU TO SURRENDER YOUR WEAPON.

11:59.980 --> 12:02.119
(vehicle door closes)

12:02.150 --> 12:04.380
NOT HERE, ALL RIGHT?

12:04.420 --> 12:06.012
IN THE CAR.

12:08.690 --> 12:11.523
JUST RELAX.
DON'T MAKE A BIG DEAL OF IT.

12:16.360 --> 12:18.362
I'M OVER HERE.

12:32.050 --> 12:33.369
(door closes)

12:35.850 --> 12:37.340
(beeps, camera shutter clicks)

12:37.390 --> 12:38.982
(radio chatter,
indistinct conversations)

12:39.020 --> 12:41.454
(clears throat) HEY, MAN.

12:41.490 --> 12:43.026
ONE EYEWITN ESS?

12:43.060 --> 12:44.084
UH, NOT REALLY.

12:44.130 --> 12:45.449
STORE OWNER WAS STANDING
IN THE DOORWAY.

12:45.490 --> 12:46.991
SAYS HE DIDN'T SEE ANYTHING.

12:47.030 --> 12:47.997
(scoffs)

12:48.030 --> 12:49.292
WHEN HE'S DONE WITH S.I.U.,

12:49.330 --> 12:50.558
I'LL TAKE HIM IN.
WE'LL HAVE A CHAT.

12:50.600 --> 12:53.160
WHAT ABOUT
THE SECURITY CAMERA?

12:53.200 --> 12:54.633
BUSTED.

12:54.670 --> 12:55.659
YEAH, OF COURSE IT IS.

12:55.700 --> 12:58.168
HEY, DID YOU GET
THE VICTIM'S GUN?

12:58.210 --> 12:59.438
(beeps and clicks)
I HAVEN'T RECOVERED THE GUN YET.

12:59.470 --> 13:01.233
(sighs)

13:01.280 --> 13:03.498
REALLY?

13:03.550 --> 13:05.609
IT'LL BE HERE SOMEWHERE.

13:05.650 --> 13:06.605
ALL RIGHT. WELL,
LET'S NOT WORRY ABOUT IT.

13:06.650 --> 13:08.072
I'M SURE WE'LL FIND IT.

13:08.120 --> 13:09.075
(footsteps approach)

13:09.120 --> 13:12.248
GENTLEM EN.
JOE FERNANDEZ, S.I.U.

13:12.290 --> 13:14.656
(clears throat)
YEAH, I'M JERRY BARBER.

13:14.690 --> 13:17.158
THIS IS SAM SWAREK.

13:17.190 --> 13:18.157
THANK YOU.

13:18.190 --> 13:20.158
OFFICER WAS ONE OF YOURS?

13:20.200 --> 13:21.827
THAT'S RIGHT. (sighs)

13:21.860 --> 13:22.827
WE'RE INVOKING OUR MANDATE.

13:22.870 --> 13:24.167
WE HAVE CONTROL
OF THE SCENE NOW.

13:24.200 --> 13:26.293
THIS IS OUR INVESTIGATION,
UNDERSTOOD?

13:26.330 --> 13:27.365
(chuckles)

13:27.400 --> 13:28.936
YOU'LL HAVE THE OPPORTUNITY
TO GET BACK IN HERE.

13:28.970 --> 13:31.438
FOR NOW, I'M GONNA ASK YOU BOTH
TO STEP OUT.

13:32.710 --> 13:36.202
I'M GONNA BE RIGHT OUTSIDE,
SO, UH, DON'T SCREW THIS UP.

13:40.380 --> 13:42.519
SO WE'RE GONNA NEED
YOUR UNIFORM

13:42.550 --> 13:44.347
AND YOUR BOOTS, TOO.

13:44.390 --> 13:45.743
THERE'S A SET OF CLOTHES
FOR YOU.

13:45.790 --> 13:48.611
THIS IS WHAT I WANT YOU TO DO.
I WANT YOU TO GET CHANGED,

13:48.660 --> 13:50.753
PUT YOUR UNIFORM
ON THE TABLE,

13:50.790 --> 13:53.429
AND THEN WAIT FOR ME
INSIDE HERE, OKAY?

13:54.860 --> 13:56.293
YES.

13:56.330 --> 13:57.297
OFFICER EPSTEIN,
YOU DO HAVE THE RIGHT

13:57.330 --> 13:58.820
TO HAVE COUNSEL PRESENT
IF YOU WISH.

13:58.870 --> 14:00.167
NO. IT'S--IT'S OKAY.

14:00.200 --> 14:02.031
IT'S, UH,
IT'S PRETTY STRAIGHTFORWARD.

14:02.070 --> 14:05.369
OKAY. I'LL SEE YOU
IN A COUPLE MINUTES.

14:24.360 --> 14:26.419
I ALREADY GAVE A STATEMENT
TO THOSE OTHER GUYS.

14:26.460 --> 14:27.996
YEAH,
THOSE OTHER GUYS WERE S.I.U.

14:28.030 --> 14:29.156
WE'RE REAL POLICE.

14:29.200 --> 14:30.861
OKAY. THANK YOU
FOR YOUR PATIENCE, MR. SANTOS.

14:30.900 --> 14:33.334
(cell phone rings)
JUST FOLLOW ME. IT WILL JUST
BE A COUPLE OF MINUTES.

14:33.370 --> 14:35.167
(cell phone beeps)

14:35.200 --> 14:37.202
FRANK, ANY WORD
FROM THE HOSPITAL?

14:37.240 --> 14:38.400
YEAH, THE KID JUST WENT
INTO SURGERY.

14:38.440 --> 14:39.464
I HAVEN'T HEARD
ANYTHING YET.

14:39.510 --> 14:40.738
WHERE'S THE WITNESS?

14:40.780 --> 14:42.975
RIGHT HERE. WE'RE JUST ABOUT
TO SIT DOWN WITH HIM.

14:43.010 --> 14:43.977
ALL RIGHT.
WELL, TAKE YOUR TIME.

14:44.010 --> 14:44.977
HE'S THE ONLY ONE
THAT KNOWS

14:45.010 --> 14:46.272
IT WAS A COP THAT PULLED
THE TRIGGER.

14:46.310 --> 14:47.618
I'M IN NO RUSH
FOR THAT INFORMATION

14:47.650 --> 14:48.617
TO COME OUT, ALL RIGHT?

14:48.650 --> 14:50.686
Yeah. I'll keep you posted.

14:50.720 --> 14:52.813
(crowd cheering)

14:52.850 --> 14:54.989
SO FAR, SO GOOD.
IT'S A PARTY.

14:55.020 --> 14:58.285
YEAH, WELL, LET'S JUST HOPE
IT STAYS THAT WAY.

14:58.330 --> 15:01.299
***

15:01.330 --> 15:03.423
(man)
* SHOOT, AND I'M SCORIN' IT *

15:03.470 --> 15:04.562
* UH-HUH *

15:04.600 --> 15:07.239
* I'M GOIN' FOR ALL OF IT *

15:07.270 --> 15:08.692
* ONE LOOSE STRAW *

15:10.110 --> 15:11.964
WE DIDN'T KNOW
IT WAS BEING ROBBED.

15:12.010 --> 15:14.137
OFFICER DIAZ STAYED
IN THE CAR.

15:14.180 --> 15:16.068
UH, AS I APPROACHED
THE STORE,

15:16.110 --> 15:19.375
THE OWNER WAS OUTSIDE
WATERING PLANTS.

15:19.410 --> 15:21.844
I WENT IN,
AND THE YOUNG MAN...

15:23.120 --> 15:24.439
DO YOU KNOW HIS NAME?

15:24.490 --> 15:25.741
TYLER MARKES.

15:27.120 --> 15:29.918
MR. MARKES
WAS BEHIND THE COUNTER.

15:29.960 --> 15:31.882
I KNEW RIGHT AWAY
SOMETHING WAS OFF.

15:31.930 --> 15:34.956
WAIT A MINUTE. HOW DID YOU
KNOW SOMETHING WAS OFF?

15:35.000 --> 15:37.321
UH, IT WAS--I JUST--
IT WAS A FEELING.

15:37.370 --> 15:39.258
HE, UH,
HE WAS BEHIND THE COUNTER.

15:39.300 --> 15:42.235
HE WAS, UM, WEARING
A HOODIE.

15:42.270 --> 15:43.931
OKAY.
JUST A FEELING,

15:43.970 --> 15:46.700
SO I ASKED HIM TO STEP OUT
FROM BEHIND THE COUNTER,

15:46.740 --> 15:50.608
AND, UM, HE--HE DIDN'T.

15:50.650 --> 15:53.039
HE, UH...

15:53.080 --> 15:55.116
SORRY. JUST...

15:55.150 --> 15:57.448
I CAN'T--ONE SECOND.

16:02.890 --> 16:05.757
HE DIDN'T. HE DUCKED DOWN
WHERE I COULDN'T SEE HIM.

16:05.790 --> 16:07.929
I CALLED FOR BACKUP.

16:07.960 --> 16:09.894
THE OWNER CAME IN
FROM OUTSIDE.

16:09.930 --> 16:11.591
THAT'S WHEN I SAW IT.

16:11.630 --> 16:15.566
HE STOOD UP, AND HE WAS
POINTING A GUN AT ME.

16:15.600 --> 16:17.909
WHAT KIND OF GUN WAS IT?

16:19.140 --> 16:20.437
I DON'T KNOW.

16:20.480 --> 16:21.629
CALIBER?

16:21.680 --> 16:22.931
I-I DON'T KNOW.

16:22.980 --> 16:24.948
WHAT ABOUT THE COLOR?

16:24.980 --> 16:27.210
BLACK? SILVER?

16:27.250 --> 16:29.411
IT WAS, UM...

16:29.450 --> 16:31.418
IT WAS NOT SILVER.
IT WAS BLACK.

16:31.450 --> 16:34.419
OKAY, SO YOU DREW
YOUR WEAPON?

16:34.460 --> 16:37.020
YES. NO. UH, IT WAS--

16:37.060 --> 16:39.187
I HAD ALREADY DRAWN IT.
IT WAS, UH...

16:39.230 --> 16:40.629
WEAPON WAS ALREADY OUT.

16:40.660 --> 16:43.959
AND WHAT HAPPENED NEXT?

16:44.000 --> 16:45.422
HE STOOD UP.

16:45.470 --> 16:47.199
HE WAS POINTING HIS GUN
AT ME,

16:47.240 --> 16:48.935
AND I SHOT HIM.

16:48.970 --> 16:50.369
HOW MANY TIMES?

16:50.410 --> 16:52.264
TWICE.

16:52.310 --> 16:53.709
WHY DID YOU STAY IN THE CAR?

16:53.740 --> 16:55.537
WHY DIDN'T YOU GO INSIDE
WITH YOUR PARTNER?

16:55.580 --> 16:58.606
UM... UH, NO REASON.

16:58.650 --> 17:00.413
UH, DOV JUST WANTED
LICORICE.

17:00.450 --> 17:02.145
I WAS JUST GONNA
WAIT OUTSIDE.

17:02.180 --> 17:03.886
IN YOUR OPINION,
DOES OFFICER EPSTEIN HAVE

17:03.920 --> 17:05.182
A SHORT TEMPER?

17:05.220 --> 17:06.642
UH...

17:06.690 --> 17:08.089
DOES HE TEND TO LOSE
HIS COOL?

17:08.120 --> 17:10.088
NO. NOT AT ALL.

17:10.130 --> 17:12.928
HAVE YOU EVER HEARD HIM MAKE
ANY RACIST STATEMENTS?

17:12.960 --> 17:14.791
WHAT?

17:14.830 --> 17:15.990
UH...

17:16.030 --> 17:18.021
THESE ARE STANDARD QUESTIONS,
OFFICER DIAZ.

17:18.070 --> 17:22.291
Y--NO. NO, UH, NEVER.

17:22.340 --> 17:24.160
OFFICER EPSTEIN,
DID YOU KNOW THE VICTIM?

17:24.210 --> 17:26.132
SORRY?

17:26.170 --> 17:28.434
HAVE YOU EVER HAD
PREVIOUS EXPERIENCE

17:28.480 --> 17:29.435
WITH THE VICTIM?

17:29.480 --> 17:31.778
NO.

17:31.810 --> 17:33.448
A WARNING?
WITNESS STATEMENTS?

17:33.480 --> 17:34.447
NO.

17:34.480 --> 17:35.845
PREVIOUS CALLS
IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD?

17:35.880 --> 17:39.247
YES, BUT THAT...

17:39.290 --> 17:40.587
OF COURSE.

17:40.620 --> 17:42.417
WERE YOU LOOKING
FOR TYLER MARKES TODAY?

17:44.790 --> 17:45.927
I'M SORRY?

17:45.960 --> 17:48.155
DID YOU INTEND
TO SHOOT HIM?

17:50.970 --> 17:53.530
I-I CHANGED MY MIND.

17:53.570 --> 17:56.459
I'D LIKE A LAWYER, PLEASE.

17:56.500 --> 17:58.058
OKAY.

18:02.610 --> 18:04.601
IT HAPPENED SO FAST.
I SAW THE COP DRAW A GUN.

18:04.650 --> 18:05.878
I PUT MY HANDS UP LIKE THIS,

18:05.910 --> 18:07.116
AND THE OTHER COP
PULLED ME BACK.

18:07.150 --> 18:08.412
DID YOU SEE THE KID?

18:08.450 --> 18:10.247
UH, N-NO, NOT REALLY.

18:10.290 --> 18:13.088
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?
DID YOU SEE HIM OR NOT?

18:13.120 --> 18:15.259
UH... JUST A SECOND.

18:15.290 --> 18:16.484
DID HE HAVE A GUN?

18:16.520 --> 18:18.579
I-I DON'T KNOW.
I DIDN'T SEE.

18:18.630 --> 18:19.927
IS HE A MEMBER OF A GANG?

18:19.960 --> 18:22.099
(chuckles) NO, NO.

18:22.130 --> 18:23.097
(chuckles)
I STAY OUT OF THAT STUFF.

18:23.130 --> 18:25.269
THAT'S NONE
OF MY BUSINESS.

18:25.300 --> 18:26.927
YOU GETTING ANYTHING
FROM THIS GUY?

18:26.970 --> 18:28.437
NO. NOT YET.

18:28.470 --> 18:30.062
HAS HE GOT A SHEET?
YEAH, HE'S GOT TWO PRIORS.

18:30.100 --> 18:31.067
(Sam and Trevor speaking
indistinctly)
I MEAN, DRUG STUFF.

18:31.110 --> 18:32.338
HE'S ON PAROLE.
(sighs)

18:32.370 --> 18:36.136
ALL RIGHT. S.I.U. TURNED
THE STORE UPSIDE DOWN. SO DID I.

18:36.180 --> 18:37.408
THERE'S NO GUN,

18:37.450 --> 18:39.406
SO UNLESS THIS GUY
STARTS TALKING,

18:39.450 --> 18:41.441
THE ONLY THING THAT PUTS
A GUN IN THE KID'S HAND...

18:41.480 --> 18:43.072
(Trevor) THAT--THAT IS
NONE OF MY BUSINESS.
IS EPSTEIN'S STATEMENT,

18:43.120 --> 18:44.678
ALL RIGHT?
MM-HMM.

18:44.720 --> 18:45.982
IT IS YOUR BUSINESS.
YOU HAVE TO PROTECT YOURSELF.
GOTTA GO.

18:46.020 --> 18:47.578
IT WOULD TAKE YOU ALL
OF TWO SECONDS TO FIND OUT

18:47.620 --> 18:48.814
IF THAT KID WAS IN A GANG.

18:48.860 --> 18:50.384
NO. (sighs) HOW MUCH LONGER
AM I GONNA BE HERE?

18:50.430 --> 18:53.024
THAT'S COMPLETELY UP TO YOU,
MR. SANTOS.

18:53.060 --> 18:54.857
LOOK, WE CAN KEEP
DOING THIS.

18:54.900 --> 18:56.424
YOU CAN KEEP TELLING US THAT
YOU DIDN'T SEE ANYTHING,

18:56.460 --> 18:58.428
BUT I GOTTA SAY,
THAT'S WHAT YOU DO,

18:58.470 --> 19:00.165
I'M GONNA BECOME
YOUR NEW BEST FRIEND.

19:00.200 --> 19:01.565
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

19:01.600 --> 19:03.465
I'M GONNA COME
TO YOUR STORE EVERY DAY,

19:03.510 --> 19:08.777
JUST TO SAY HI, YOU KNOW,
CHAT, LAUGH.

19:08.810 --> 19:10.107
I'M GONNA MAKE SURE

19:10.140 --> 19:12.279
THAT EVERY SINGLE PERSON
IN YOUR NEIGHBORHOOD KNOWS

19:12.310 --> 19:15.017
JUST HOW TIGHT YOU ARE
WITH THE COPS.

19:15.050 --> 19:16.972
(chuckles)
THIS IS HARASSMENT.

19:17.020 --> 19:18.339
SIT DOWN.

19:23.160 --> 19:26.425
MR. SANTOS,
I KNOW YOU'RE SCARED.

19:26.460 --> 19:28.257
JUST TELL US THE TRUTH.

19:28.300 --> 19:30.427
YOU SAW TYLER MARKES HAD A GUN.

19:30.470 --> 19:33.394
YOU SAW HE WAS ABOUT TO SHOOT
OFFICER EPSTEIN.

19:34.970 --> 19:38.428
NO. HE WASN'T.

19:38.470 --> 19:40.438
THE KID WASN'T ARMED.
HE WAS CLEAN.

19:40.480 --> 19:42.937
YOU WANT TO KNOW WHAT I SAW?

19:42.980 --> 19:46.643
I SAW A COP SHOOT A KID
IN COLD BLOOD.

19:48.820 --> 19:51.243
SO WHO'S GOT A PROBLEM
WITH THE NEIGHBORHOOD NOW?

19:53.320 --> 19:55.880
I WATCHED THAT KID GROW UP.

19:55.920 --> 19:59.083
TYLER--I KNEW HIM
HIS WHOLE LIFE.

19:59.130 --> 20:01.724
MY CONDOLENCES, JONES.

20:01.760 --> 20:04.263
***

20:04.300 --> 20:06.723
ARE YOU SURE THERE'S NOTHING
YOU WANNA TELL ME, FRANK?

20:06.770 --> 20:07.930
YOU KNOW,
THIS INFORMATION THING,

20:07.970 --> 20:09.437
I'M THINKING, SHOULD BE
A 2-WAY STREET--

20:09.470 --> 20:11.609
GIVE AND TAKE.

20:11.640 --> 20:12.937
MEANING WHAT?

20:12.970 --> 20:15.006
MEANING THAT MAYBE IT WAS
A COP THAT SHOT THAT BOY.

20:15.040 --> 20:17.076
WAS YOUR BOY GANGED UP?

20:17.110 --> 20:18.941
NOW THAT'S NOT THE POINT.

20:18.980 --> 20:20.948
IF IT IS A COP
AND THEY FIND OUT,

20:20.980 --> 20:22.413
THERE'S GONNA BE
TROUBLE, FRANK.

20:22.450 --> 20:25.089
YOU CAN BELIEVE THAT.
TROUBLE.

20:25.120 --> 20:28.214
(crowd cheering
and shouting indistinctly)

20:28.260 --> 20:30.581
WE'RE NOT FEELING
THE LOVE HERE, SIR.

20:30.630 --> 20:32.257
CAN I MAKE A SUGGESTION?

20:32.290 --> 20:34.099
WE COULD SHUT THIS WHOLE THING
DOWN RIGHT NOW, SIR.

20:34.130 --> 20:35.256
THERE'S A LOT OF PEOPLE HERE.

20:35.300 --> 20:36.927
ANY OF THESE GUYS HAVE
AUTOMATIC WEAPONS--

20:36.960 --> 20:38.666
HEY. THEY BELONG TO A GANG.

20:38.700 --> 20:40.565
THAT DOESN'T MAKE 'EM
BARBARIC OR STUPID.

20:41.870 --> 20:43.838
STAY ON CHANNEL 3.

20:50.010 --> 20:51.272
(indistinct conversations)

20:51.310 --> 20:54.313
(telephone ringing in distance,
radio chatter)

20:59.790 --> 21:02.213
(buzzer)

21:07.460 --> 21:09.792
HEY. H-HOW'D IT GO?

21:09.830 --> 21:11.388
FINE. YOU?

21:11.430 --> 21:12.397
(exhales deeply)
I DON'T KNOW, MAN.

21:12.430 --> 21:14.091
THE, UH, THE QUESTIONS--

21:14.140 --> 21:16.358
THEY WERE...
THEY WERE PRETTY CRAZY.

21:16.400 --> 21:18.504
IT'S OKAY. THEY'RE JUST
DOING THEIR JOB.

21:20.710 --> 21:22.769
HAVE WE, UH, HEARD ANYTHING
FROM THE HOSPITAL YET?

21:22.810 --> 21:24.277
YEAH, UH...

21:24.310 --> 21:26.778
HE DIDN'T MAKE IT.

21:26.810 --> 21:28.516
HE DIED IN SURGERY.

21:29.550 --> 21:31.279
I'M SORRY, DOV.

21:35.620 --> 21:37.622
HEY, DOV.

21:38.790 --> 21:41.588
IT GETS WORSE.

21:41.630 --> 21:43.996
THEY CAN'T FIND THE GUN.

21:49.000 --> 21:51.059
WE'RE GONNA KEEP LOOKIN'...

21:53.070 --> 21:54.628
BUT WE NEED TO TALK
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENS

21:54.680 --> 21:57.478
IF WE DON'T RECOVER
THAT GUN AT THE SCENE.

21:59.680 --> 22:01.944
SO... (clears throat)

22:01.980 --> 22:06.417
THE WORST-CASE SCENARIO
IS THAT THEY FIND THAT

22:06.450 --> 22:10.113
YOUR LIFE WAS NOT IN DANGER
AND YOU USED EXCESSIVE FORCE.

22:10.160 --> 22:11.582
(sighs)
THAT DOESN'T SOUND GOOD.

22:11.630 --> 22:14.451
HEY, DON'T WORRY ABOUT THAT.
WE'RE NOT THERE YET,

22:14.500 --> 22:16.718
BUT WE HAVE TO BE PREPARED
FOR THE WORST.

22:20.970 --> 22:22.892
SO, EPSTEIN, THE KID...

22:24.640 --> 22:26.039
HE HAD A GUN?

22:26.070 --> 22:28.436
YES.

22:28.480 --> 22:30.129
YOU'RE SURE?

22:38.620 --> 22:40.349
WHAT HAPPENS IF HE DIDN'T?

22:40.390 --> 22:41.755
(inhales deeply)

22:41.790 --> 22:42.779
(clears throat and sighs)

22:42.820 --> 22:49.555
***

22:54.070 --> 22:55.765
(indistinct conversations,
radio chatter)

22:55.800 --> 22:58.803
(telephone ringing in distance)

23:01.380 --> 23:02.802
JERRY'S LOOKING FOR YOU.

23:02.840 --> 23:05.673
YEAH, I KNOW.
HE'S CALLED ME 15 TIMES.

23:05.710 --> 23:06.699
LOOK, UM...

23:06.750 --> 23:08.377
I DON'T KNOW. I-I DON'T.

23:08.420 --> 23:09.739
I CAN'T REMEMBER
WHAT I SAW ANYMORE.

23:09.780 --> 23:11.338
I MEAN, I-I'M TRYING,
BUT I--

23:11.390 --> 23:12.448
DOV, YOU SAW A GUN.

23:12.490 --> 23:14.082
YEAH, BUT WHAT IF HE DIDN'T
HAVE ONE?

23:14.120 --> 23:17.055
HOW DO I LIVE WITH THAT?
WHAT DO I DO WITH THAT?

23:17.090 --> 23:19.422
I THINK YOU KNOW
WHAT YOU SAW.

23:19.460 --> 23:22.327
YOU KNOW,
WE ALL BELIEVE YOU,

23:22.360 --> 23:24.828
BUT, YOU KNOW,
IF IT TURNS OUT THAT

23:24.870 --> 23:28.465
IT WASN'T QUITE LIKE THAT,

23:28.500 --> 23:32.209
THEN, UH...
WE'LL WORK FROM THAT.

23:37.550 --> 23:40.519
(indistinct conversations)

23:40.550 --> 23:41.517
(door closes)

23:41.550 --> 23:43.484
(buzzer in distance)

23:43.520 --> 23:45.181
HEY.

23:45.720 --> 23:47.039
HEY. WHERE IS HE?

23:47.090 --> 23:48.580
HE'S, UH, HE'S IN THE GYM.

23:48.620 --> 23:50.110
HE'S STARTING TO DOUBT
HIS OWN MEMORY.

23:50.160 --> 23:51.718
(lowered voice)
THIS WHOLE THING COULD TURN.

23:51.760 --> 23:52.829
I WANT
TO TALK TO THE WITNESS.

23:52.860 --> 23:53.827
YOU CAN'T.

23:53.860 --> 23:54.827
YOU CAN'T GO NEAR HIM.

23:54.860 --> 23:56.259
UH, HE WAS RIGHT THERE.

23:56.300 --> 23:58.268
I MEAN, I PULLED HIM
OUT OF THE STORE.

23:58.300 --> 24:01.337
HE MUST HAVE SEEN EVERYTHING.
WHY WOULD HE LIE ABOUT THAT?

24:01.370 --> 24:03.338
(telephone ringing in distance)

24:03.370 --> 24:05.008
WHAT?

24:05.040 --> 24:07.008
(chair wheels rattle)

24:07.040 --> 24:10.840
JERRY. (lowered voice)
WHAT'S HAPPENING WITH DOV?

24:10.880 --> 24:13.519
WELL, ASSUMING I CAN
FIND HIM,

24:13.550 --> 24:14.517
I'M GONNA WALK HIM
THROUGH IT

24:14.550 --> 24:16.609
AND TRY AND DETERMINE
SOME FACTS.

24:16.650 --> 24:18.686
DO YOU BELIEVE HIS STORY?

24:18.720 --> 24:20.039
DOESN'T MATTER
WHAT I BELIEVE.

24:20.090 --> 24:23.651
JERRY, HE SAW A GUN.

24:23.690 --> 24:26.818
YOU WANT TO BE A DETECTIVE,
START THINKING LIKE ONE,

24:26.860 --> 24:28.396
WHICH MEANS YOU DON'T FORM
A CONCLUSION

24:28.430 --> 24:29.658
AND FIND EVIDENCE
TO SUPPORT IT.

24:29.700 --> 24:32.294
YOU ESTABLISH FACTS,
AND THEN YOU FOLLOW THEM.

24:32.330 --> 24:33.638
YOU SEE WHERE THEY TAKE YOU.

24:33.670 --> 24:34.830
OKAY, BUT THIS IS DOV--

24:34.870 --> 24:37.634
NO, NO, NO.
QUESTION EVERYTHING.

24:37.670 --> 24:39.604
DOUBT EVERYTHING.

24:39.640 --> 24:42.200
HE HAD A SECOND TO FORM
A JUDGMENT, MAYBE LESS.

24:42.240 --> 24:43.639
IT COULD HAVE BEEN A GUN
IN THE KID'S HAND,

24:43.680 --> 24:45.102
BUT IT COULD HAVE BEEN
A PHONE.

24:45.150 --> 24:47.675
IT COULD HAVE BEEN NOTHING.

24:47.720 --> 24:51.383
LOOK, I WANT TO BELIEVE HIM,

24:51.420 --> 24:53.479
BUT I GOT A JOB TO DO.

24:53.520 --> 24:55.078
SO DO YOU.

24:56.620 --> 24:58.554
SO I'VE BEEN GOING
THROUGH YOUR FILE.

24:58.590 --> 25:00.126
YOU'VE GOT TWO CONVICTIONS--
POSSESSION,

25:00.160 --> 25:01.957
POSSESSION
FOR THE PURPOSE OF.

25:02.000 --> 25:05.026
WENT TO JAIL FOR TWO YEARS.
I MEAN, VERY STRAIGHTFORWARD,

25:05.070 --> 25:08.198
BUT THEN I NOTICED THIS.

25:08.240 --> 25:11.129
I MEAN,
THESE ARE INCIDENT REPORTS.

25:11.170 --> 25:13.809
YOUR STORE HAS BEEN ROBBED
17 TIMES IN THE LAST 2 YEARS.

25:13.840 --> 25:15.171
SO?

25:15.210 --> 25:16.871
WELL, DID YOU HAVE A GUN
IN THE STORE, MR. SANTOS?

25:16.910 --> 25:18.241
MAYBE BEHIND THE COUNTER?

25:18.280 --> 25:19.872
(chuckles) NO. NO WAY.

25:19.910 --> 25:20.877
ARE YOU SURE?

25:20.920 --> 25:22.114
YEAH, I'M SURE.

25:22.150 --> 25:23.549
YEAH. NO, I'D PROBABLY SAY
THE SAME THING, TOO,

25:23.590 --> 25:24.579
IF I WERE YOU,

25:24.620 --> 25:27.180
I MEAN, GIVEN
THAT YOU'RE ON PAROLE,

25:27.220 --> 25:29.108
BECAUSE, YOU KNOW,
IF YOU HAD A GUN,

25:29.160 --> 25:31.924
YOU WOULD BE GOING
STRAIGHT BACK TO PRISON.

25:31.960 --> 25:33.450
THAT'S WHAT TYLER WAS AFTER.

25:33.490 --> 25:35.958
HE KNEW THERE WAS A GUN,
WENT IN TO STEAL IT,

25:36.000 --> 25:37.797
MAYBE EVEN USE IT TO ROB
THE PLACE,

25:37.830 --> 25:40.469
BUT HE DIDN'T GET THAT FAR,
AND THIS GUY IS LYING.

25:40.500 --> 25:42.968
BECAUSE HE'S ON PAROLE.

25:43.000 --> 25:45.036
THE ONLY PROBLEM IS
THERE'S NO GUN.

25:45.070 --> 25:46.765
SO LET'S GO BACK,
HAVE ANOTHER LOOK.

25:46.810 --> 25:50.200
YEAH, IT'S NOT THERE, SAM.
WE'RE NOT GONNA FIND IT.

25:50.240 --> 25:51.207
(Trevor, filtered voice)
HOW MANY TIMES DO I HAVE

25:51.250 --> 25:52.205
TO SAY THIS?

25:52.250 --> 25:54.309
THERE WAS NO GUN.

25:54.350 --> 25:56.375
I DON'T KNOW.
I'M PSYCHING MYSELF OUT.

25:56.420 --> 25:58.388
I KEEP THINKING
SOMEBODY'S GONNA COME

25:58.420 --> 26:00.786
OUT OF NOWHERE AND JUST,
LIKE, TAKE IT FROM ME.

26:00.820 --> 26:02.549
NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

26:02.590 --> 26:05.957
WELL, I HOPE NOT. (sighs)

26:05.990 --> 26:06.957
(sighs)

26:06.990 --> 26:09.129
BUT ONE OF THE COURSES
THAT I TOOK,

26:09.160 --> 26:12.129
PRINCIPLES OF INTERROGATION,

26:12.170 --> 26:14.934
I LEARNED THIS TECHNIQUE THAT'S
SUPPOSED TO HELP WITNESSES

26:14.970 --> 26:17.438
SEE THINGS
A LITTLE BIT MORE CLEARLY.

26:17.470 --> 26:20.200
WHAT, YOU WANT
TO TRY IT OUT ON ME?

26:20.240 --> 26:21.639
I DO.

26:22.710 --> 26:24.439
YEAH, OKAY.
KNOCK YOURSELF OUT.

26:24.480 --> 26:26.277
OKAY. SIT DOWN.
WHAT DO--

26:26.310 --> 26:27.811
OKAY.

26:29.320 --> 26:33.086
JUST, LIKE, GET COMFORTABLE.
MAKE YOURSELF COMFORTABLE...

26:33.120 --> 26:36.510
(sighs)
AND CLOSE YOUR EYES.

26:36.560 --> 26:38.687
CLOSE YOUR EYES.

26:38.730 --> 26:40.322
(sighs)

26:44.300 --> 26:46.120
OKAY.

26:46.170 --> 26:48.730
NOW PUT YOURSELF BACK
AT THE SCENE.

26:50.100 --> 26:52.864
OKAY. YOU'VE JUST ARRIVED
AT THE STORE.

26:52.910 --> 26:54.798
NOW TELL ME...

26:54.840 --> 26:57.377
NOT WHAT YOU SEE,

26:57.410 --> 27:00.607
BUT TELL ME WHAT YOU FEEL,
WHAT YOU HEAR.

27:00.650 --> 27:02.777
WHAT DO YOU SMELL?

27:02.820 --> 27:04.788
UH, I SMELL DETERGENT.

27:05.990 --> 27:09.380
THERE'S FISH
THAT'S A LITTLE BIT OFF

27:09.420 --> 27:11.320
IN THE FREEZER.

27:11.360 --> 27:13.248
OKAY. THAT'S GOOD.
THAT'S GOOD. WHAT DO YOU HEAR?

27:13.290 --> 27:14.689
I HEAR TRAFFIC.

27:14.730 --> 27:16.948
(engine rumbles)
A MOTORCYCLE.

27:17.000 --> 27:19.468
I HEAR, UH, SOMETHING
ON THE RADIO.

27:19.500 --> 27:22.060
I CAN'T MAKE OUT
EXACTLY WHAT,

27:22.100 --> 27:23.636
UH, AND THEN THE OWNER
IS YELLING.

27:23.670 --> 27:24.762
I TELL HIM TO SHUT UP.

27:24.810 --> 27:28.302
DISPATCH IS IN MY WALKIE,
AND...

27:29.310 --> 27:30.436
THAT'S IT.

27:30.480 --> 27:32.107
OKAY. FEEL.
WHAT DO YOU FEEL?

27:33.980 --> 27:36.119
MY HAND...

27:36.150 --> 27:37.742
IS ON MY GUN,

27:37.790 --> 27:40.987
ON THE GRIP.
I PULL IT FROM MY HOLSTER.

27:43.490 --> 27:46.084
I'M SCARED
FOR A SECOND, FROZEN.

27:46.130 --> 27:49.395
THEN I JUMP BACK,
AND I HIT... A SHELF.

27:49.430 --> 27:51.159
S-SOMETHING FALLS
FROM THE SHELF,

27:51.200 --> 27:52.861
HITS THE FLOOR.

27:55.540 --> 27:57.735
MY FINGER...

27:57.770 --> 27:59.032
TOUCHES THE TRIGGER.

27:59.070 --> 28:00.435
I SQUEEZE.

28:00.470 --> 28:02.938
THE GUN BUCKS HARD,
LIKE A PUNCH.

28:02.980 --> 28:04.641
BAM!
(gunshot)

28:08.150 --> 28:11.039
SECOND SHOT'S SOFTER,
LIKE, UH...

28:11.090 --> 28:12.045
MORE LIKE A POP.

28:12.090 --> 28:15.287
(gunshot)

28:15.320 --> 28:17.652
WHY DID THEY SOUND
DIFFERENT?

28:18.990 --> 28:21.129
I DON'T KNOW.
MY EARS WERE RINGING AND...

28:21.160 --> 28:22.798
HOW MANY TIMES DID YOU FIRE?

28:22.830 --> 28:26.527
TWICE. I TOLD YOU.
BANG! POP.

28:26.570 --> 28:29.459
WELL, IS IT POSSIBLE
THAT HE FIRED, TOO?

28:31.170 --> 28:33.934
(Ski Beatz's "This World"
Playing)

28:33.980 --> 28:36.778
(sighs) DOV MUST BE FREAKING
OUT RIGHT NOW.

28:36.810 --> 28:37.947
* THEY SAY FOOLISH PRIDE *

28:37.980 --> 28:40.778
(sighs) I WASN'T EXPECTING
THIS COMING BACK.

28:40.820 --> 28:43.118
THOUGHT IT WOULD BE
A BIT MORE...

28:43.150 --> 28:45.118
PEACEFUL?

28:45.150 --> 28:47.038
GUYS, HEY.

28:47.090 --> 28:48.682
WOULD YOU MIND LIFTING UP
YOUR SHIRTS FOR ME, PLEASE?

28:48.720 --> 28:49.687
(chuckles)
YEAH, THIS ISN'T KANDAHAR.

28:49.720 --> 28:51.051
COME ON.
COME ON. INDULGE ME.

28:51.090 --> 28:52.682
JUST LIFI' 'EM UP AND SWIVEL.
(glass shatters)

28:52.730 --> 28:54.891
* BUT I'M COMFORTABLE
IN MY OWN SKIN *

28:54.930 --> 28:56.488
(radio static)
UH, 1521.

28:56.530 --> 28:58.691
WE'RE NEAR ST. JAMES
AND BLEECKER.

28:58.730 --> 29:00.459
SOMEONE JUST THREW
A SHOPPING CART AT US.

29:00.500 --> 29:01.967
(static)
(man) TURN AROUND
AND DON'T COME BACK!

29:02.000 --> 29:05.766
(radio chatter,
people shouting indistinctly)

29:05.810 --> 29:09.598
***

29:09.640 --> 29:11.107
PEOPLE ARE LEAVING.
THEY'RE SCARED.

29:11.150 --> 29:13.448
YEAH. I WANT YOU OUT OF HERE.
I WANT YOU BACK AT THE PRECINCT.

29:13.480 --> 29:14.549
FRANK, KNOCK IT OFF.

29:14.580 --> 29:15.774
HEY, I OUTRANK YOU.

29:15.820 --> 29:17.117
IF YOU DON'T LIKE IT,
FILE A GRIEVANCE.

29:17.150 --> 29:19.448
WAIT RIGHT HERE
FOR A SECOND. ROLAND.

29:19.490 --> 29:20.741
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

29:20.790 --> 29:23.179
LISTEN, PEOPLE ARE LEAVING,

29:23.220 --> 29:24.448
AND MY MEN ARE UNDER ATTACK.
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?

29:24.490 --> 29:25.457
I HAVE NOTHING TO SAY
TO YOU.

29:25.490 --> 29:28.129
HEY, LISTEN.

29:28.160 --> 29:29.457
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU, FRANK?

29:29.500 --> 29:30.626
IT DOESN'T MATTER
TO YOU NO MORE,

29:30.660 --> 29:32.366
AS LONG AS WE'RE SHOOTING
EACH OTHER.

29:32.400 --> 29:33.628
IS THAT HOW IT IS?

29:33.670 --> 29:35.638
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
WHAT AM I TALKING ABOUT?

29:35.670 --> 29:38.309
YOU KNEW ALL ALONG
IT WASN'T A GANG SHOOTING.

29:38.340 --> 29:41.434
YOU KNEW IT...
(whispers) ALL ALONG.

29:41.480 --> 29:42.936
(normal voice)
YOU KNOW WHAT?

29:42.980 --> 29:44.902
IT'S A COP THAT SHOT TYLER.

29:44.950 --> 29:46.474
IT WAS A COP
THAT SHOT TYLER!

29:46.510 --> 29:47.579
AND ONE OF YOURS.
WHERE DID YOU HEAR THAT FROM?

29:47.610 --> 29:48.611
IT DON'T MATTER
WHERE I HEARD IT FROM.

29:48.650 --> 29:49.776
TAKE YOUR HANDS OFF ME.
YOU KNOW WHAT?

29:49.820 --> 29:52.243
IF YOU WANT, YOU ARREST ME.
ARREST ME!

29:52.290 --> 29:53.609
* KIDS GETTIN' KIDNAPPED
IN BROAD DAY *

29:53.650 --> 29:54.617
* GUNS GETTIN' PUT *

29:54.660 --> 29:55.718
ALL RIGHT.

29:55.760 --> 29:57.113
THEN I GUESS
WE'RE DONE HERE.

29:57.160 --> 29:58.787
* ENEMIES WHERE YOU LIVE AT *

29:58.830 --> 30:00.457
COME ON. WE'RE DONE.

30:00.490 --> 30:03.459
***

30:03.500 --> 30:04.967
* LIKE A TOURIST *

30:05.000 --> 30:06.297
WHAT WAS THAT?

30:06.330 --> 30:08.139
(crowd cheering)

30:08.170 --> 30:11.435
THINGS JUST WENT FROM BAD
TO WORSE.

30:14.610 --> 30:16.032
SO DOV WAS ABOUT... HERE?

30:16.080 --> 30:17.968
NO, UH, TAKE A STEP BACK.

30:18.010 --> 30:19.079
(radio chatter)

30:19.110 --> 30:21.010
I'M TYLER.
I'M BEHIND THE COUNTER.

30:21.050 --> 30:23.439
DUCK DOWN.

30:23.480 --> 30:25.243
I COME BACK UP. BOOM!

30:29.820 --> 30:32.721
OKAY, GUYS. I GET IT. ALL RIGHT.
YOU TRUST YOUR FRIEND.

30:32.760 --> 30:33.897
YOU WANT TO BELIEVE HIM.

30:33.930 --> 30:35.397
DOV'S BEEN OVER
THESE TWO OR THREE SECONDS

30:35.430 --> 30:36.897
A THOUSAND TIMES,

30:36.930 --> 30:38.227
AND EACH TIME,
IT GETS LESS CLEAR.

30:38.270 --> 30:39.567
I GOT SOMETHING.

30:39.600 --> 30:40.669
SERIOUSLY?

30:40.700 --> 30:41.667
YEAH. RIGHT HERE.

30:41.700 --> 30:42.837
LET'S SEE.

30:42.870 --> 30:44.838
(clicks)

30:44.870 --> 30:47.566
OH. YEAH, YOU DO.

30:47.610 --> 30:49.373
(plastic rustling)

30:49.410 --> 30:50.377
GOT IT?

30:50.410 --> 30:51.843
YEP.

30:55.520 --> 30:58.546
OKAY, WE GOT A BULLET.
WHERE'S THE GUN?

30:58.590 --> 30:59.784
IT'S GOTTA BE HERE.

30:59.820 --> 31:01.549
WELL, IT ISN'T,
BECAUSE WE'VE LOOKED.

31:01.590 --> 31:03.785
NOW THIS PLACE HAS BEEN
ROBBED 17 TIMES.

31:03.820 --> 31:06.618
ANY ONE OF THOSE TIMES
COULD ACCOUNT FOR THAT BULLET.

31:08.630 --> 31:10.848
TYLER FELL HERE.

31:12.770 --> 31:14.829
ANDY, STAND WHERE
DOV WAS AGAIN.

31:14.870 --> 31:16.895
OKAY.

31:16.940 --> 31:19.067
CAN YOU SEE ME RIGHT NOW?

31:19.110 --> 31:20.236
NO.

31:22.240 --> 31:23.400
HOW ABOUT NOW?

31:23.440 --> 31:25.078
NO.

31:30.580 --> 31:32.138
WHAT ABOUT NOW?

31:36.920 --> 31:38.182
THERE WERE TWO OF THEM.

31:38.230 --> 31:39.686
THERE WAS SOMEONE ELSE
BEHIND THE COUNTER.

31:39.730 --> 31:41.618
HE WAS CROUCHED DOWN,
SO DOV COULDN'T SEE HIM.

31:41.660 --> 31:44.527
SO TYLER GETS SHOT,
OTHER GUY PICKS UP THE GUN.

31:44.570 --> 31:45.662
AND THEN RUNS OUT
THE BACK DOOR.

31:45.700 --> 31:47.793
(sighs)
THERE WAS A THIRD MAN.

31:47.830 --> 31:49.832
IT'S POSSIBLE.

31:51.710 --> 31:53.337
IT'S POSSIBLE.

31:59.350 --> 32:01.215
I ASSUME YOU'RE HERE TO TELL US
WHO SHOT MY BROTHER.

32:01.250 --> 32:02.877
WE'RE STILL WORKING ON THAT.

32:02.920 --> 32:04.615
(sighs)
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN--
"YOU'RE STILL WORKING ON IT"?

32:04.650 --> 32:06.584
CRYSTAL.
BECAUSE WE HEARD
IT WAS A COP.

32:06.620 --> 32:09.851
WE--WE CAN'T GIVE ANY DETAILS
RIGHT NOW. I'M SORRY.

32:09.890 --> 32:11.983
UH, TYLER'S FRIENDS--
WAS THERE ANYONE,

32:12.030 --> 32:14.055
UH, HE SPENT A LOT
OF TIME WITH,

32:14.100 --> 32:15.795
MAYBE GOT
INTO A LITTLE TROUBLE WITH?

32:15.830 --> 32:16.922
YOU'RE TRYING TO PUT THIS
ON MY BROTHER.

32:16.960 --> 32:18.029
(Sam) UH, NO.

32:18.070 --> 32:19.469
YOU'RE SAYING
I-IT WAS HIS FAULT.

32:19.500 --> 32:20.797
NO, NO.
WE JUST WANT TO FIND OUT

32:20.830 --> 32:23.663
IF SOMEONE ELSE WAS THERE
WHO SAW WHAT HAPPENED.

32:23.700 --> 32:26.703
THEY'RE TALKING ABOUT CORY.

32:26.740 --> 32:28.105
CORY BARN ES.

32:28.140 --> 32:29.437
THEY'VE BEEN BEST FRIENDS
SINCE GRADE TWO.

32:29.480 --> 32:32.449
THEY DID EVERYTHING
TOGETHER.

32:32.480 --> 32:34.641
CORY'S BEEN ARRESTED
A COUPLE OF TIMES.

32:34.680 --> 32:37.114
UH, DO YOU HAVE
AN ADDRESS FOR CORY?

32:37.150 --> 32:39.118
OH, I'M NOT GONNA SPEAK
FOR CORY.

32:39.150 --> 32:40.481
CORY CAN SPEAK FOR HIMSELF.

32:40.520 --> 32:41.817
(papers rustling)
I'LL GET YOU HIS NUMBER.

32:41.860 --> 32:47.321
MOM, DON'T BOTHER.
THEY DON'T CARE.

32:47.360 --> 32:49.157
THAN KS.
UH, YEAH.

32:49.200 --> 32:51.327
THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR YOUR TIME.

32:51.370 --> 32:53.691
IF ANYTHING COMES UP,
WE'LL DEFINITELY LET YOU KNOW.

32:53.730 --> 32:55.834
I'M TRYING HARD
TO BELIEVE YOU.

32:55.870 --> 32:57.189
IN THIS NEIGHBORHOOD,
MOST OF THE TIME,

32:57.240 --> 32:58.502
POLICE ARE THE ENEMY.

33:00.610 --> 33:02.703
WE'RE REALLY SORRY
ABOUT YOUR SON

33:02.740 --> 33:03.707
AND YOUR BROTHER.

33:03.740 --> 33:06.379
(door creaks)

33:06.410 --> 33:08.469
(door closes)

33:08.520 --> 33:11.944
(engine rumbles)

33:11.990 --> 33:12.979
(car door Opens)

33:18.460 --> 33:19.586
(amplified voice)
I WANT TO THANK EVERYBODY

33:19.630 --> 33:20.881
FOR COMING OUT
AND SUPPORTING THE NEIGHBORHOOD.

33:20.930 --> 33:21.897
GIVE YOURSELVES A HAND.

33:21.930 --> 33:23.090
(cheers and applause)

33:23.130 --> 33:24.893
WE ARE PULLING THE PLUG
ON THIS TOURNAMENT.

33:24.930 --> 33:27.398
I WANT EVERYONE OUT
OF THIS PARK NOW.

33:27.430 --> 33:31.560
OKAY. BE CALM. STAY FIRM.
DO NOT BACK DOWN.

33:31.610 --> 33:34.408
ALL RIGHT, FOLKS.
THE PARTY'S OVER.

33:34.440 --> 33:36.408
COME ON. EVERYONE OUT.
LET'S GO.

33:36.440 --> 33:38.806
EVERYONE LEAVE THE PARK
AND GO HOME, OKAY?

33:38.850 --> 33:40.306
FOR WHAT? WE LIVE HERE.

33:40.350 --> 33:42.648
RIGHT. TURN AROUND
AND START WALKING.

33:42.680 --> 33:44.386
OR WHAT?
HE'S NOT ASKING.

33:44.420 --> 33:46.081
OH, YEAH?
WHAT, YOU GONNA SHOOT ME, TOO?

33:46.120 --> 33:47.815
ALL RIGHT. THAT'S ENOUGH.
HEY, HEY.

33:47.850 --> 33:50.887
ROLAND, JUST ASK YOUR FRIENDS
TO LEAVE, PLEASE.

33:50.920 --> 33:53.354
(indistinct conversations)

33:53.390 --> 33:54.789
WHOA. EASY, EASY.

33:56.600 --> 33:57.749
COME ON, ROLAND.

33:57.800 --> 33:59.461
(siren wailing in distance)
IT'S OVER, MAN.

33:59.500 --> 34:01.491
I DON'T THINK SO.

34:01.540 --> 34:02.632
(grunts)
HEY! HEY, HEY, HEY!

34:02.670 --> 34:04.809
(all shouting at once)

34:04.840 --> 34:07.559
AAH! (grunts and pants)

34:07.610 --> 34:09.032
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.
THIS IS OVER.
(batons click)

34:09.080 --> 34:10.308
THIS IS OVER.

34:10.340 --> 34:12.706
GO HOME.

34:12.750 --> 34:14.047
GO HOME.

34:15.120 --> 34:17.748
OR JOIN YOUR PAL IN A 4X6.

34:17.780 --> 34:18.747
(handcuffs rattle)

34:18.790 --> 34:20.212
FRANK!
(panting) YEAH.

34:20.250 --> 34:21.217
(handcuffs click)
YOU GOOD?

34:21.260 --> 34:22.352
(grunts)
I'M DOWN!

34:22.390 --> 34:23.414
GET HIM OUT OF HERE.
GET HIM OUT OF HERE!

34:23.460 --> 34:25.428
(radio static)
DISPATCH, THIS IS 1519.

34:25.460 --> 34:26.427
(static)
KEEP MOVING. KEEP WALKING.

34:26.460 --> 34:27.757
GET IN YOUR CARS AND GO.

34:27.790 --> 34:28.757
GET UP!

34:28.800 --> 34:29.892
YOU OKAY?
(Noelle) YEAH.

34:29.930 --> 34:33.229
MOVE IT! (grunts)

34:33.270 --> 34:34.794
(sighs)

34:34.840 --> 34:37.729
THIS KID'S ONLY 17.
HE ALREADY HAS 3 CONVICT IONS.

34:37.770 --> 34:39.135
WELL, HE'S CERTAINLY GOT
THE RIGHT ADDRESS.

34:39.170 --> 34:40.137
(clicks and beeps)

34:40.170 --> 34:41.671
THIS BUILDING'S NOTORIOUS.

34:41.710 --> 34:45.840
BEEN LIT UP WITH GUN CALLS
AND DRUG BUSTS FOR YEARS.

34:48.520 --> 34:50.977
SAM, BEHIND US.
I THINK THAT'S HIM.

34:51.020 --> 34:52.487
THE GRAY HOODIE.

34:52.520 --> 34:53.782
YEP.

35:03.260 --> 35:04.397
STAY WITH HIM, MCNALLY!

35:04.430 --> 35:05.761
OKAY!

35:13.770 --> 35:15.579
SIR, MOVE!

35:15.610 --> 35:19.102
(panﬁng)

35:30.890 --> 35:33.723
NO MORE RUNNING TODAY.

35:33.760 --> 35:36.649
THAT'S IT.

35:36.700 --> 35:37.655
HOW YA DOIN', PARTNER?
(handcuffs clicking)

35:37.700 --> 35:39.668
CAN YOU GIVE HIM
A PAT-DOWN, PLEASE?

35:39.700 --> 35:41.167
(panﬁng)

35:41.200 --> 35:43.168
LET'S GET THAT HAND THERE.

35:43.200 --> 35:45.031
HEY.

35:48.840 --> 35:50.478
(sighs)

35:50.510 --> 35:51.647
(chuckles)

35:51.680 --> 35:53.648
YOU KNOW WHAT, JON ESY?

35:53.680 --> 35:54.647
(handcuffs click)
YOU STILL HERE?

35:54.680 --> 35:55.647
(chuckles)
ONE WEEK,

35:55.680 --> 35:57.477
FRESH OUT OF THE HOLE.

35:57.520 --> 35:58.544
(lowered voice)
YOU COULD HAVE WALKED AWAY.

35:58.590 --> 35:59.682
MAN, YOU KNOW WHAT, FRANK?
(clatters)

35:59.720 --> 36:01.210
IF THERE EVER WAS
A MISTAKE MADE...

36:01.260 --> 36:02.386
(clatters)
(chuckles)
IT WAS TALKING TO YOU

36:02.420 --> 36:03.785
IN THE _FIRST PLACE.
(radio chatter)

36:03.820 --> 36:05.048
(scoffs) YEAH.

36:05.090 --> 36:06.955
TELL SERGEANT SHAW
I'LL BE BACK FOR THAT, EH?

36:06.990 --> 36:09.720
(chuckles) YO, STAFF SERGEANT,
YOU SHOULD BE THANKING ME.

36:09.760 --> 36:10.727
(rattles)

36:10.760 --> 36:12.068
I HELPED YOUR ASS OUT, MAN.

36:12.100 --> 36:13.567
MY ASS?
YEAH.

36:13.600 --> 36:15.568
IT WAS ALL ABOUT YOU, JONESY.
WHA--WHAT? (scoffs)

36:15.600 --> 36:16.635
IT WAS ALL ABOUT YOU

36:16.670 --> 36:19.138
TRYING TO BUY YOURSELF
SOME STREET CRED.

36:21.580 --> 36:24.845
I STILL HELPED YOU OUT,
MAN... (scoffs) EASY.
(handcuffs click)

36:24.880 --> 36:28.441
I TOOK THE PRESSURE OFF.
HOLD ON A SECOND.

36:28.480 --> 36:31.017
ME AND YOU--WE GO WAY BACK.

36:31.050 --> 36:34.110
COME ON, MAN. THINK YOU CAN
CUT ME SOME SLACK, HUH?

36:34.150 --> 36:35.879
(radio chatter)

36:35.920 --> 36:39.219
(rattles and clanks)

36:39.260 --> 36:41.125
(keys jangling)
(Sighs)

36:41.160 --> 36:43.025
MAYBE I WILL.

36:43.060 --> 36:44.925
(handcuffs click)

36:44.970 --> 36:47.165
(knocks on door)

36:47.200 --> 36:49.862
EPSTEIN. GOOD. COME IN.

36:52.210 --> 36:53.507
YOU RECOGNIZE
THIS YOUNG MAN?

36:53.540 --> 36:55.132
(door closes)
NO, SIR.

36:55.180 --> 36:58.638
WELL, HE WAS IN THE STORE
WITH YOU THIS MORNING,

36:58.680 --> 37:01.046
AND HE RAN OUT THE BACK...

37:01.080 --> 37:02.741
WITH THIS.

37:04.250 --> 37:05.547
.38 SNUB NOSE.

37:05.590 --> 37:07.546
BALLISTICS MATCHED IT
TO A BULLET

37:07.590 --> 37:09.581
WE FOUND IN THE STORE.

37:11.760 --> 37:12.727
(plastic rustles)

37:12.760 --> 37:14.557
IT WAS A GOOD SHOOT.

37:15.760 --> 37:18.422
THANK YOU.

37:18.470 --> 37:21.735
(door opens)

37:21.770 --> 37:23.761
(door creaks and closes)

37:28.140 --> 37:29.801
(knocks)

37:29.840 --> 37:32.274
YOU WANTED TO SEE ME, SIR?

37:32.310 --> 37:34.619
WELL, YOU GOT IT, NASH.

37:34.650 --> 37:37.073
THE ROTATION--
IT'S YOURS IF YOU WANT IT.

37:37.120 --> 37:39.088
I WANT IT. (chuckles)

37:39.120 --> 37:40.917
GOOD. GOOD.

37:40.950 --> 37:43.009
YOU'RE THE BEST PROSPECT
WE'VE SEEN IN A LONG TIME.

37:43.060 --> 37:45.119
THANK YOU, SIR.

37:45.160 --> 37:47.924
ALL RIGHT.
THANK YOU. (chuckles)

37:47.960 --> 37:50.952
(indistinct conversations,
radio chatter)

37:52.800 --> 37:54.939
DON'T EXPECT ME
TO GO EASY ON YOU.

37:54.970 --> 37:58.428
YOUR FIRST DAY, I'M GONNA OPEN
A BIG OL' CAN OF WHUP-ASS.

37:58.470 --> 38:00.006
(laughing)

38:00.040 --> 38:01.837
ALL RIGHT.
LET'S CELEBRATE.

38:01.880 --> 38:03.302
I'M THINKING
SOMETHING BUBBLY.

38:03.340 --> 38:05.479
(sighs) YOU KNOW,
IT'S BEEN A LONG DAY,

38:05.510 --> 38:08.149
AND I KINDA WANT TO GO HOME
AND SEE LEO.

38:08.180 --> 38:09.317
YEAH, I'M GOOD WITH THAT.

38:09.350 --> 38:11.147
OKAY.

38:11.180 --> 38:14.479
YOU ARE HAPPY, THOUGH, RIGHT,
ABOUT THE ROTATION? I MEAN...

38:14.520 --> 38:17.409
YEAH. AREN'T YOU?

38:17.460 --> 38:21.180
YEAH. YEAH.
NO, IT'S GONNA BE GREAT.

38:21.230 --> 38:22.219
(chuckles)

38:22.260 --> 38:24.660
OKAY. I'LL SEE YOU
AT THE CAR.

38:24.700 --> 38:25.667
OKAY. (chuckles)

38:25.700 --> 38:28.168
YOU TOTALLY DESERVE IT.

38:28.200 --> 38:30.168
I SHOULD NEVER HAVE
EVEN APPLIED.

38:30.200 --> 38:31.838
THEN WHY DID YOU?

38:31.870 --> 38:34.509
WELL, 'CAUSE I'M A PECK,
AND THERE ARE...

38:34.540 --> 38:36.838
CERTAIN EXPECTATIONS
THAT GO WITH THE NAME.

38:36.880 --> 38:38.131
PECKSPECTATIONS?

38:38.180 --> 38:39.408
(whispers) YEAH.

38:39.450 --> 38:41.748
(laughs, normal voice)
YOU--YOU ARE SO LUCKY, TRACI.

38:41.780 --> 38:43.270
YOU KNOW EXACTLY
WHAT YOU WANT.

39:06.710 --> 39:09.975
(buzzer)

39:10.010 --> 39:10.977
HEY.

39:11.010 --> 39:11.977
YOU READY?

39:12.010 --> 39:13.705
YEAH, I GUESS YOU WERE RIGHT.

39:13.750 --> 39:14.717
ABOUT WHAT?

39:14.750 --> 39:16.149
REALITY.

39:16.180 --> 39:18.648
DOV SLAMMED
RIGHT INTO IT TODAY.

39:18.690 --> 39:19.884
YOU KNOW, YOU'RE RIGHT.
YOU EXPECT THE WORST...

39:19.920 --> 39:21.148
(sighs)
AND YOU'LL NEVER BE
DISAPPOINTED.

39:21.190 --> 39:23.249
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?
YOU BELIEVED IN HIM.

39:23.290 --> 39:25.758
IF DOV'S CLEAR,
IT'S BECAUSE OF YOU GUYS.

39:25.790 --> 39:27.189
YEAH.

39:29.030 --> 39:29.997
YOU COMIN' OVER?

39:30.030 --> 39:32.169
(scoffs) THAT'S OPTIMISM.

39:32.200 --> 39:33.667
NAH, THAT'S EXPERIENCE.

39:33.700 --> 39:36.032
(chuckles)

39:36.070 --> 39:39.062
(water running in showers,
women speaking indistinctly)

39:42.540 --> 39:45.475
(lowered voice) HEY.
I'M NOT HERE TO CONTROL YOU.

39:45.510 --> 39:46.807
I JUST WANT
TO KEEP YOU SAFE.

39:46.850 --> 39:48.715
(clanks)
I KNOW.

39:48.750 --> 39:49.717
LOOK, NOELLE, IT IS D--

39:49.750 --> 39:51.843
I KNOW, OKAY?

39:51.890 --> 39:53.539
I-I GET IT.

39:54.560 --> 39:56.516
I GOT SCARED TODAY.

39:56.560 --> 39:57.811
I ACTUALLY GOT SCARED.

39:57.860 --> 39:59.987
I MEAN...

40:00.030 --> 40:02.999
SOME NUMB-NUTS KNOCKS ME DOWN,
AND ALL I CAN THINK ABOUT

40:03.030 --> 40:05.066
IS LOSING WHAT I NEVER
THOUGHT I'D HAVE...

40:07.130 --> 40:11.908
SO FROM ON, I WILL RIDE
THE DESK, ALL RIGHT?

40:11.940 --> 40:13.669
AND I WILL EVEN TRY
AND LIKE IT.

40:14.740 --> 40:16.435
NO, YOU WON'T.

40:17.680 --> 40:20.148
NO, YOU'LL HATE IT,
EVERY BIT OF IT.

40:20.180 --> 40:21.613
YEP.

40:23.350 --> 40:24.487
ALL RIGHT.

40:27.190 --> 40:28.657
(latch clicks)

40:28.690 --> 40:31.318
(radio chatter)

40:31.360 --> 40:32.622
(thunder rumbles)

40:32.660 --> 40:33.888
NIGHT, GUYS.

40:33.930 --> 40:37.457
(man) * WHEN THE SUN BREAKS
YOUR WINDOWS *

40:39.600 --> 40:43.263
* AND SHATTERS YOUR EYES *

40:43.300 --> 40:46.599
* YOU REALIZE *

40:46.640 --> 40:48.938
(thunder rumbling)

40:48.980 --> 40:51.437
(honks horn)

40:59.190 --> 41:00.839
GET IN.

41:06.430 --> 41:08.318
(closes door)

41:08.360 --> 41:10.225
WE NEED TO LAY SOME
SERIOUS GROUND RULES, OKAY?

41:10.260 --> 41:11.329
OKAY.

41:11.360 --> 41:13.669
DON'T LOOK AT ME,
DON'T TOUCH ME,

41:13.700 --> 41:15.338
AND DON'T GIVE ME
THOSE, LIKE,

41:15.370 --> 41:17.395
REALLY WEIRD, CREEPY,
MEANINGFUL LOOKS.

41:17.440 --> 41:19.431
AM I ALLOWED TO RECALL
WHAT YOU LOOK LIKE NAKED?

41:19.470 --> 41:21.108
DO YOU WANT ME TO PUNCH YOU
IN THE FACE?

41:21.140 --> 41:23.301
* ...MISSIN' *

41:23.340 --> 41:24.807
(sighs)

41:24.850 --> 41:29.310
* YOU'VE NOT YET REPLACED *

41:29.350 --> 41:31.147
(keys jangle, starts engine)

41:31.180 --> 41:32.647
(shifts gears)

41:32.690 --> 41:35.011
* SWEETH EART *

41:36.290 --> 41:39.555
* WHAT I'M TRYING TO SAY *

41:41.960 --> 41:46.420
* IS ALL THAT I'M FEELIN' *

41:46.470 --> 41:47.767
(thunder rumbling)

41:47.800 --> 41:50.769
* WITH WORDS IN THE WAY *

41:50.800 --> 41:54.429
* THAT YOU ARE A BIRD *

41:54.470 --> 41:56.574
* AND YOU SOARED *

41:56.610 --> 41:58.373
WERE YOU A FRIEND?

41:58.410 --> 41:59.809
I'M SORRY?

41:59.850 --> 42:01.943
OF TYLER'S.

42:01.980 --> 42:03.208
DID YOU KNOW HIM?

42:03.250 --> 42:04.547
* IN MY VEINS *

42:04.590 --> 42:06.319
NO.

42:06.350 --> 42:08.318
NO, UH, I WAS JUST...

42:08.350 --> 42:10.011
PASSING BY.

42:13.660 --> 42:15.457
(thunder rumbles)
